# Investment Growth Chart

## Author
Jeremiah E. Ochepo

## Last Updated
February 15, 2020 (7 PM)

## Description
This program calculates and visualizes the growth of a 10-year investment based on the initial principal and annualized interest rate provided by the user. The growth is represented by a bar chart, showing the investment value for each year.

## How to Use
1. Run the program.
2. Enter the initial principal amount when prompted.
3. Enter the annualized interest rate when prompted.
4. Enter the number of years for which you want to observe the investment growth.
5. Observe the graphical representation of the investment growth in the window that appears.
6. Press <Enter> to close the window and quit the program.

## Features
- The program provides a visual representation of the investment growth using a simple bar chart.
- Labels on the left edge of the chart indicate different monetary values.
- The user is prompted to input the initial principal, annualized interest rate, and the number of years.
- The program calculates and displays the investment value for each year.
- The graphical window allows users to visually understand the growth pattern.

## Requirements
- Python 3.x
- graphics module (Ensure the graphics module is installed: `pip install graphics.py`)

## Example

The program will generate a graphical window displaying the investment growth over the specified number of years.

## Note
- Make sure the `graphics` module is installed. You can install it using `pip install graphics.py`.

Enjoy exploring your investment growth!

